             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>ᚏᚌ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>ᚁᚉ<supplied reason="lost">ᚐ</supplied>ᚏᚉᚓᚅ</persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>RG<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>BC<supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>RCEN</persName>
                </ab>
                <ab type="list">[.?.]RG[.?.]BC[A]RCEN</ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note>According to Macalister (1945, 286), <q>There was doubtless an A between the B and the R. CEN is certain - four small nicks represent the vowel - but obviously the inscription is past restoration</q>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>No translation can be provided.</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The extant inscription is too short to support analysis.</p>
            </div>
